=3D"https://www.sensorsone.com/psi-pounds-per-square-inch-pressure-unit/">p=
si</a> =3D 6,894.76 pascals (Pa)</li>
<li>1 <a href=3D"https://www.sensorsone.com/inhg-inch-of-mercury-0-deg-c-pr=
essure-unit/">inHg</a> =3D 3386.39 pascals (Pa)</li>
<li>psi value x 6,894.76 Pa =3D inHg value x 3,386.39 Pa</li>
<li><strong>psi value =3D inH<span style=3D"font-size: 15px;">g</span> valu=
e / 2.03602</strong></li>
